Indian /ˈɪndɪən/

(Indians) 

1. ADJ Indian means belonging or relating to India, or to its people or culture. 印度的; 印度人的; 印度文化的 [usu ADJ n] 

例： ...the Indian government. ...印度政府。 

2. N-COUNT An Indian is an Indian citizen, or a person of Indian origin. 印度人; 印度裔 

3. N-COUNT Indians are the people who lived in North, South, or Central America before Europeans arrived, or people living today who are descended from them. Another name for them now is Native Americans . 印第安人

